article.headline: Army 92, SUNY Maritime 42
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Matt Bell had 19 points to lead Army in a 92-42 win over Maritime Monday night. Army dominated the game early on, finishing the first half with a 58-14 lead. Jimmy Sewell and Jarell Brown added 10 each for the Black Knights (9-2). Timothy Dougherty scored 18 points and had eight rebounds to lead Maritime (1-7), but he was the only player in double digits. Army outrebounded the Privateers 43-31. The Black Knights shot 60.9 percent for the game, compared to Maritime's 25.4 percent. The game sealed Army's first six-game winning streak since the 1984-85 season.
